<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5565&amp;p=24787#p24787</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5565&amp;p=24787#p24787"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: In Classic Start Menu Please Initially Focus On All Prog]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5565&amp;p=24787#p24787"><![CDATA[
You can do a simple trick to quickly show the All Programs menu since you are using the Classic style.<br /><br />Go to Customize Start Menu tab and double click on the &quot;Programs&quot; item to bring up the &quot;Edit Menu Item&quot; dialog.<br /><br />Erase everything from the Label field and enter this:<br />&amp; Programs<br /><br />(Note that there is an ampersand i.e.'&amp;' character followed by a SPACE and then the text 'Programs'). Click OK.<br /><br />Now go to the &quot;Search Box&quot; tab and uncheck the option &quot;Selected by default&quot;. Click OK to close the Settings dialog.<br /><br />Now you can press Win key, followed by the Space bar to quickly open the &quot;All Programs&quot; menu. Train yourself to use Space bar instead of the Enter/Return key. It is easier to access in fact since it's the biggest key on the keyboard.<br /><br />The search box can still be focused quickly by pressing the Tab key.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Tue Jan 26, 2016 11:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
