<title type="html"><![CDATA[In Classic Start Menu Please Initially Focus On All Programs]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5565&amp;p=24399#p24399"><![CDATA[
This is a <strong>Feature Request</strong>.<br /><br />I run Windows 7 x64.<br /><br />In the <strong>Settings for Classic Start Menu 4.2.4</strong> --&gt; <strong>Start Menu Style</strong> tab, I have selected <strong>Classic style</strong>. In the <strong>Controls</strong> tab, <strong>Windows Start Menu</strong> is the <strong>default start menu</strong>. In the list of <strong>...opens:</strong> items, I have selected <strong>Windows Key opens: Classic Start Menu</strong> and <strong>Shift+Win opens: Windows Start Menu.</strong><br /><br />In the <strong>Windows Start Menu</strong> tab, I have the <strong>Cascading All Programs menu</strong> set to <strong>Initially focus on: All Programs.</strong> For me, this initial focus is very productive for quickly displaying the <strong>All Programs</strong> menu.<br /><br /><br />Because I want to alter and use the <strong>Classic Start Menu</strong>, I would like it to also place the initial focus on <strong>All Programs</strong>, which it does not do now. In fact, the initial focus does not appear anywhere, as repeatedly pressing the Return key produces no response.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=381">RetiredEngineer</a> — Thu Jan 07, 2016 7:13 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
